	<text>
		<body>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><date>Friday</date></p>
				<p>&#8220;Why did <persName>Moses</persName> delay going down from the mountain&#8221;&#63; Why has there<lb/> been no answer&#63; You have received a fine piece of work. I beg of you<lb/> to accept at once both the German as well as the postscript&#44; and also<lb/> to translate in to English. Include it in the following number. In<lb/> the postscript against <persName>Szold</persName> and <persName>Einhorn</persName>&#44; I want to swat two flies at<lb/> once. <sic>Isay</sic> that when one man is a rascal it does not mean that the <lb/> other is too. About <persName>Szold</persName> we do not know at all what he hold to.<lb/> <persName>Einhorn</persName>&#44; at least&#44; said definitely what he wants.  For this he de&#45;<lb/>serves thanks. &#8220;And thou shalt make a fence around thy roof&#8221;. Nothing<lb/> in this postscript should seem unnatural to him. &#8220;The wise man has<lb/> his eyes in his head&#8221;. But I must urgently request that you send me<lb/> the proof sheets. I shall return them to you at once&#44; and there will<lb/> be no delay. The articles are very important for our interests.<lb/> That you will discover upon mature consideration. Only such language<lb/> is effective. I therefore ask you to print the entire sermon and the<lb/> postscript in one issue. You will be able to sell separate numbers<lb/> of it. That is why a quarter of a sheet more will not be injurious<lb/> Set up the galley and prepare an English translation of the sermon.<lb/> Send me at lease ten copies of this issue. <persName>Szold&#39;s</persName> defense of the<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Minhag <placeName>America</placeName></hi> is shameful and is completely contrary to <persName>Wise</persName>. As<lb/> I point out in the notes <del>&#63;</del> in calm language&#44; one must stroke<lb/> playfully without scratching. &#8220;This is the manner of <sic>theTorah</sic>&#8221; <persName>Ein&#45;<lb/>horn</persName> does you much honor. He calls you the old lion. It is good<lb/> that you can roar while he can only shout. Do no write against it.<lb/> &#8220;I shall answer my traducers&#8221;.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Berend</persName> is crazy. Don&#39;t accept anything <sic>fromhim</sic>. He puts<lb/> <persName>Jesus</persName> on an equal plane with <persName>Moses</persName>. He is an ignoramus and in the<lb/> highest degree confused. At his <date>Sunday</date> services&#44; there was &#8220;no man<lb/> and no response&#8221;. I must end because of the approach of the <date>Sabbath</date>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Your friend who respects you with a</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">sincere heart&#44; which</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">wails like a dove.</p>
				<p>All the remarks on <sic>themargin</sic> of the pages belong to the text&#44; except<lb/> where the word <hi rend="underline">note</hi> is written nearby. That belongs below the text.<lb/> There are only two notes&#45; one in the sermon itself and one in the<lb/> postscript. I urgently ask you to take the greatest care in the<lb/> setting up.</p>
		</body>
